{"parse":{"title":"Post-graduate diploma in management studies (UK)","pageid":14202291,"revid":822790137,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>\nThe <b>post-graduate diploma in management studies</b>, <a href=\"/wiki/Post-nominal_letters\" title=\"Post-nominal letters\">post-nominal letters</a> <b>DMS</b>, is a university management qualification in the United Kingdom.\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><input type=\"checkbox\" role=\"button\" id=\"toctogglecheckbox\" class=\"toctogglecheckbox\" style=\"display:none\" /><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2><span class=\"toctogglespan\"><label class=\"toctogglelabel\" for=\"toctogglecheckbox\"></label></span></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#History\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">History</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#Early_structure\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1.1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Early structure</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#Entry_requirements\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1.2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Entry requirements</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#Accreditation\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1.3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Accreditation</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#Assessment\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1.4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Assessment</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-6\"><a href=\"#Controversy\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Controversy</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-7\"><a href=\"#Recognition\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Recognition</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-8\"><a href=\"#See_also\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">See also</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-9\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">5</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"History\">History</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Post-graduate_diploma_in_management_studies_(UK)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: History\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Early_structure\">Early structure</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Post-graduate_diploma_in_management_studies_(UK)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: Early structure\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>The post-graduate qualification was originally accredited by the DMS Committee of the <a href=\"/wiki/Department_of_Education_and_Science_(UK)\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Department of Education and Science (UK)\">DES</a>. It originally required either one year full-time or 3 years part-time study, and was arranged in two discrete sections: Part A and Part B. It was compulsory to pass the Part A examinations and assessment first before being allowed to take Part B. Part B consisted of the final examinations and a project dissertation. Overall the marks achieved in coursework, examinations and the final dissertation had to exceed a weighted threshold for the candidate to pass and be awarded a DMS. It was thus quite an intensive course with a large workload. If a candidate achieved 90% or above, they were awarded a Distinction.\n</p>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Entry_requirements\">Entry requirements</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Post-graduate_diploma_in_management_studies_(UK)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=\"Edit section: Entry requirements\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>Normally a bachelor's degree or extensive managerial experience and/or other professional qualifications. Originally there was also a lower age limit for entry of 35 years old, but this requirement was subsequently dropped as managers above that age found that the qualification had no value in achieving employment or promotion above 35.\n</p>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Accreditation\">Accreditation</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Post-graduate_diploma_in_management_studies_(UK)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" title=\"Edit section: Accreditation\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>Initially in the UK the qualification was accredited by the DMS committee of the DES, and later by the <a href=\"/wiki/Council_for_National_Academic_Awards\" title=\"Council for National Academic Awards\">Council for National Academic Awards</a> (CNAA). It was originally accepted by the <a href=\"/wiki/Chartered_Management_Institute\" title=\"Chartered Management Institute\">BIM</a> as its core qualification for admission as a full member. The BIM subsequently was renamed to the Institute of Management when combining with the Institute of Industrial Managers, and now has again been renamed to become the <a href=\"/wiki/Chartered_Management_Institute\" title=\"Chartered Management Institute\">Chartered Management Institute</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Assessment\">Assessment</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Post-graduate_diploma_in_management_studies_(UK)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5\" title=\"Edit section: Assessment\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>The assessment for the few DMS courses which are still run in the UK is now almost without any formal examinations being required to be passed. It is thus subjectively awarded on the basis of course performance only, according to the opinion of the academic staff responsible.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Controversy\">Controversy</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Post-graduate_diploma_in_management_studies_(UK)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=6\" title=\"Edit section: Controversy\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>It has been argued by some that the move away from mainly or wholly exam assessed courses has lessened the 'value of the qualification' however the change from exams to coursework, projects and assignments is fairly in keeping with most postgraduate UK qualifications, although some exams are normally required.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Recognition\">Recognition</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Post-graduate_diploma_in_management_studies_(UK)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=7\" title=\"Edit section: Recognition\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>The DMS is accepted by the CMI as part of the required qualification for <a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Chartered_manager&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Chartered manager (page does not exist)\">chartered manager</a>.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"See_also\">See also</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Post-graduate_diploma_in_management_studies_(UK)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=8\" title=\"Edit section: See also\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><a href=\"/wiki/Master_of_business_administration\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Master of business administration\">Master of business administration</a></li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Post-graduate_diploma_in_management_studies_(UK)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=9\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.managers.org.uk\">CIM</a></span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n\n<!-- \nNewPP limit report\nParsed by mw1328\nCached time: 20180907181128\nCache expiry: 1900800\nDynamic content: false\nCPU time usage: 0.032 seconds\nReal time usage: 0.050 seconds\nPreprocessor visited node count: 192/1000000\nPreprocessor generated node count: 0/1500000\nPost\u2010expand include size: 1066/2097152 bytes\nTemplate argument size: 226/2097152 bytes\nHighest expansion depth: 12/40\nExpensive parser function count: 1/500\nUnstrip recursion depth: 0/20\nUnstrip post\u2010expand size: 368/5000000 bytes\nNumber of Wikibase entities loaded: 0/400\nLua time usage: 0.004/10.000 seconds\nLua memory usage: 664 KB/50 MB\n-->\n<!--\nTransclusion expansion time report (%,ms,calls,template)\n100.00%   37.264      1 -total\n 72.58%   27.045      1 Template:Use_dmy_dates\n 27.28%   10.164      1 Template:DMCA\n 24.11%    8.983      1 Template:Reflist\n 22.57%    8.410      1 Template:Dated_maintenance_category\n 14.73%    5.489      1 Template:FULLROOTPAGENAME\n  9.78%    3.646      1 Template:Ns_has_subpages\n  5.75%    2.144      1 Template:Main_other\n-->\n\n<!-- Saved in parser cache with key enwiki:pcache:idhash:14202291-0!canonica